  "text_preview": "ASL sunday ASL Lessons | Bookstore | Library | ASL University Main ► American Sign Language: \"Sunday\" The sign for \" Sunday \" has several popular versions. SUNDAY: (version) Hold your hands up about head high and then move your right hand in a clockwise circle and your left hand in a counterclockwise circle as if you were washing a window with both hands: SUNDAY: (Other version) Hold your hands up, palms forward, \"5 handshapes\" in front of and to the sides of your head. Bring them down to your torso area. The movement from top to bottom forms a backwards arc . SUNDAY: (Yet another version.) This version starts at your torso, arcs in a bit (back towards your chest) and out again at about head height. EVERY SUNDAY: In this version of the sign, when you bring the hands down you bring them str"
}
